<item>
            <title>[LU-737] can not attach device name starting with a digit</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-737</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If we assign fsname starting with a digit (ie 1b), the OST devices name will be 1b-OST0000 and this will prevent lctl to work, see below&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;root@fat-amd-1 ~&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;# lctl dl&lt;br/&gt;
  0 UP mgs MGS MGS 5&lt;br/&gt;
  1 UP mgc MGC10.10.4.132@tcp 299348e4-2002-b4b5-3a43-44db755a662a 5&lt;br/&gt;
  2 UP mdt MDS MDS_uuid 3&lt;br/&gt;
  3 UP lov 1b-mdtlov 1b-mdtlov_UUID 4&lt;br/&gt;
  4 UP mds 1b-MDT0000 1b-MDT0000_UUID 3&lt;br/&gt;
  5 UP ost OSS OSS_uuid 3&lt;br/&gt;
  6 UP obdfilter 1b-OST0000 1b-OST0000_UUID 5&lt;br/&gt;
  7 UP osc 1b-OST0000-osc 1b-mdtlov_UUID 5&lt;br/&gt;
  8 AT echo_client 1b-OST0000_ecc 1b-OST0000_ecc_UUID 1&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;root@fat-amd-1 ~&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;# lctl&lt;br/&gt;
lctl &amp;gt; device 1b-OST0000_ecc&lt;br/&gt;
lctl &amp;gt; cleanup&lt;br/&gt;
cleanup: please use &apos;device name&apos; to set the device name for config commands.&lt;br/&gt;
lctl &amp;gt; &lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;I also found out that lustre fsname can be anything except &quot;:&quot;. is this a good idea? should we restrict it to unix name format (alpha, number, _)?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
